{
  "texts": [
    "Firstly, we show that SimCLR required a more significant number of FLOPs as the encoder in the learning pipeline was used multiple times for each transformation.",
    "Also, we found that MAE and data2vec significantly required fewer FLOPs, again with the iSPL model.",
    "HART required much fewer FLOPs than iSPL for almost all methods.",
    "In terms of parameter counts, we see an opposite trend where the parameters of the supervised and SimCLR are about half less than those of other methods.",
    "Due to the encoder-decoder and siamese configuration of MAE and Data2vec, their number of parameters are about double that of the supervised and SimCLR."
  ]
}